## ✨ Features

- 🔀 **Intent-based routing** — a Switch node directs each message to the correct agent (Force / Nexus / Victor / Team / Sizu).
- 🧩 **Specialized AI agents** — every agent has its own system prompt, model, memory, and tools.
- 🌐 **Multi-model support** — Google Gemini, Groq, and OpenRouter run side by side, so you pick the right model per task.
- 🧠 **Shared conversational memory** — a Simple Memory node keeps context consistent across agents.
- 🤝 **Sub-agents (Team Force & Team Nexus)** — top-level agents delegate to sub-agents for deeper, multi-step reasoning.
- 📧 **Gmail integration** — the default agent can read inbox messages and answer questions about them.
- 🧱 **Parallel execution + Merge** — multiple agents can run in parallel; their outputs are merged into one structured response.
- 🪄 **Post-processing layer** — a JavaScript Code node cleans, formats, and structures the final reply before sending it back to Telegram.

