## 🏗️ Architecture

| Component | Role |
|---|---|
| **Telegram Trigger** | Captures every incoming message from the user |
| **Switch (Rules mode)** | Reads the message and routes to one of 5 agents |
| **Ai Force** | Action/execution-focused agent (Gemini) — delegates to Team Force |
| **Ai Nexus** | Connector/integration agent (OpenRouter) — delegates to Team Nexus |
| **Ai Victor** | Analytical agent (Groq — fast inference) |
| **Ai Victor1** | Secondary analytical agent (Groq) for follow-up reasoning |
| **Ai Default** | Fallback agent with Gmail tool access |
| **Team Force / Team Nexus** | Sub-agents for multi-step, deeper task handling |
| **Simple Memory** | Shared conversational context across agents |
| **Merge (append)** | Combines outputs from up to 3 parallel agent runs |
| **Code in JavaScript** | Formats and cleans the final reply |
| **Send a Text Message** | Delivers the final reply back to the Telegram user |

---

## 🤖 The Agents

### 1. Ai Force — `Gemini`
The "doer." Handles task execution, generation, and action-oriented requests. Delegates complex jobs to **Team Force** sub-agent.

### 2. Ai Nexus — `OpenRouter`
The "connector." Bridges different data sources and integrations. Hands off multi-tool flows to **Team Nexus** sub-agent.

### 3. Ai Victor / Ai Victor1 — `Groq`
The "thinkers." Use Groq for ultra-fast inference on reasoning, summaries, and follow-ups.

### 4. Ai Default — `Groq + Gmail Tool`
The "concierge." Picks up anything not matched by the router and can read Gmail to answer mailbox-related queries.

### 5. Sizu Route *(reserved)*
A reserved channel for the operator (Saizul) — admin-level commands and meta-operations on the workflow itself.

